The paper deals with scheduling problems, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and optimization and control (cs.RO). The use of Galvin's theorem suggests a connection to graph theory (cs.CC), and the use of routing and edge-weighted graphs suggests a connection to network optimization (cs.GT).
